                            <p class="Para">This paper demonstrates that work in digital enterprises— like work in conventional enterprises—can be carried out effectively by <em class="EmphasisTypeItalic ">autonomous agents</em>, subject to a regulatory regime that combines standing enterprise-wide policies with flexible managerial controls. The proposed regulatory mechanism, which is based on the concept of Law Governed Interaction (LGI), can support a wide range of enterprise policies, and a wide spectrum of managerial styles—including the procedural style underlying the so called Workflow Management System (WfMS).</p>
